          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Neutron emission  cross  sections  have been measured",
                " for  targets  of  6Li,  7Li,  10B,  14N,   and   16O",
                " irradiated  with  x-rays  in  energy range from 7 to",
                " almost 30 MeV.",
                "The integrated   cross   sections   are   0.40(0.03),",
                " 0.49(0.04), 0.44(0.03), 0.42(0.03) and 0.26(0.02) in",
                " units of the classical dipole sum.",
                "The average  cross sections for the lithium and boron",
                " targets appear to be  essentially  constant  in  the",
                " energy range 25-30 MeV.",
                "The data also suggest that the boron  cross  sections",
                " contains  a  great  deal  of  structure  up  to the",
                " highest energies studied."
              ]
            }
          ],
